Kim Kardashian has been likened to Marilyn Monroe by Carine Roitfeld.The former French Vogue editor, who now edits her own title, CR Fashion Book, explained why she cast the newly-engaged reality star, 33, in her latest issue.Ms Roitfeld told Time Out London: 'She’s controversial, but so was Marilyn
Monroe and I always like controversial people.' A modern Marilyn Monroe? Kim Kardashian has been likened to the late icon by Carine Roitfeld, who featured her on the cover of her magazine CR Fashion Book
Dividing opinion: Monroe, pictured in 1953. The former French Vogue editor said of Ms Kardashian: 'She's controversial, but so was Marilyn Monroe and I always like controversial people'
The photo shoot saw the heavily-pregnant Kardashian pose for Karl Lagerfeld back in May, in a shoot art-directed by Riccardo Tisci. She was seen wearing a grill on the magazine cover, while inside shots showed her with jam smeared across her mouth and an embellished mask over her face. More...
They're engaged! Kanye West proposes to Kim Kardashian on her birthday with a huge 15-carat diamond ring... and he rents out ENTIRE baseball park to pop the question
Out with the old and in with the new! How does Kim Kardashian's 15-carat sparkler from Kanye West size up to the 20-carat bling she received from ex-Kris Humphries?
Another image shows her in a black veil and a Yankees cap, while a further frame shows her baring her seven-months-pregnant belly with pride. Tastemaker: Ms Roitfeld, pictured at the Met Gala in May, says Ms Kardashian's beauty is a 'talent'
'She was brave. . . with Karl Lagerfeld shooting,' Ms Roitfeld continued. 'She had one guy for hair, one guy for make-up – no extensions or lashes – and for her it must have been like being naked, and she accepted everything.'I
don’t think normally she would wear those sort of clothes – I’ve never seen her in a Comme des Garcons jumpsuit or a basketball jacket, but she
said yes to everything. She was the easiest model we’ve had. And when we put a mask on her face, she didn’t say anything.'Ms Roitfeld added that she considers Ms Kardashian's beauty a 'talent' and also praised her work ethic.'She’s beautiful – and in fashion, that is a talent you know,' she said. 'She was also a very sweet person, a hard worker. You don’t see her
in parties drinking loads of alcohol.'Ms Kardashian, who got engaged to boyfriend Kanye West in an elaborate proposal last night, features in the third issue of CR Fashion Book.Roitfeld told WWD that the image was a 'precious moment of Kim’s pregnancy that people haven’t seen.' And, she insists, her feature on Ms Kardashian is a far cry from the weekly magazines that charted every stage of her pregnancy. 'Brave': Ms Kardashian's face is smeared with jam in the shoot by Karl Lagerfeld for CR Fashion Book
Mirror image: The reality star pictured with and without a heavily-embellished mask 'Precious moment': The reality star, who was expecting baby North at the time of the May shoot, is seen baring her seven-months-pregnant belly with pride
'This is not something for a gossip magazine that goes into the trash. This is a magazine that is a collector’s item,' she said.'I hope the issue will be
a good souvenir for her and her baby,' she added to Time Out.The new issue of CR Fashion Book is on newsstands now.
